Preconditions:
The `root` parameter must not be null.
The `sum` parameter must be a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return `true` if there exists a root-to-leaf path in the binary tree such that the sum of all values along the path is equal to the `targetSum`.
The method should return `false` if no such path exists in the binary tree.
The binary tree structure should not be modified by the method.
The method should not have any side effects on the binary tree.